<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-179-818  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 179 818.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  April 10 1989 v6 n14 p71(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>How to head off hackers. (network security) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fermazin, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies must build security safeguards into their voice mailsystems to prevent the invasion of hackers.andP;  Using an 800 numberto access a voice mail system invites trouble.andP;  Hackers canprogram a computer to repeatedly call a voice mail system to trydifferent passwords until one gives them access to a voicemailbox.andP;  Once inside the mailbox, hackers set up their ownpassword and leave messages for other hackers.andP;  Close attentionshould be paid to activity on a system, in particular thosemailboxes which can be accessed through an 800 number.andP;  Passwordsshould have at least six characters and should be changedperiodically.andP;  Systems are available to augment security.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Voice MailSecuritym PasswordsGuidelinesComputer HackersNetworksLocal Area Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>